I'm not sure if this is the right place but the dev docs (<https://developers.HubSpot.com/en/docs/cms/building-blocks/module-theme-fields>) for module &amp; theme fields is missing the `visibility` attribute for color field types, `font` has it but `color` doesn't.

e.g. this is what the HubSpot boilerplate generates has for `fields.json`

```        "label": "Primary color",
        "name": "primary_color",
        "type": "color",
        "visibility": {
          "hidden_subfields": {
            "opacity": true
          }
        }, ```

I managed to circumvent the issue by doing this, but it is kind of jank and I hate it, so if anyone has a better idea let me know :sweat_smile:
```{% set default_array = module.cards|selectattr('card_front.text','containing', request.query_dict['search-'+ name]) %}
  {% set lower_array = module.cards|selectattr('card_front.text','containing', request.query_dict['search-'+ name]|lower) %}
  {% set title_array = module.cards|selectattr('card_front.text','containing', request.query_dict['search-'+ name]|title) %}
  {% set item_array = default_array + lower_array + title_array %}
{{item_array|unique}}```
